        q: `A 55-year-old man has smoked two packs of cigarettes per day for 35 years. For the past 4 years, he has had a chronic cough with copious mucoid expectoration. During the past year, he has had multiple respiratory tract infections diagnosed as “viral flu.” He has also developed difficulty breathing, tightness of the chest, and audible wheezing. His breathing difficulty is relieved by inhalation of a β-adrenergic agonist and disappears after the chest infection has resolved. Which of the following pathologic changes is most likely to be present in this patient?`,
